[White "Playing against e4:  The Alekhine"]
[Black "4 Pawns attack:  White finishes development"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. c4 Nb6 5. f4
{ A critical line against the Alekhines. White attempts to swamp Black in the centre.  At first I was going to recommend 5...g6 here, but the main line scores well and is very respectable. }
5... dxe5 6. fxe5 Nc6 7. Be3 Bf5 8. Nc3 e6 9. Nf3 Be7 10. Be2
{ 10 d5 is critical.  This gives Black time to finish development.  It is also the most common move at low levels. }
10... O-O 11. O-O f6 12. exf6 Bxf6 13. Qd2 Qe7 14. Rad1 Rad8
{ Black will probably now play h6, Bh7 and Kh8.  Black is fine, but be careful not to play...e5 too early. }
