1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. c4 Nb6 5. f4
{ A critical line against the Alekhines. White attempts to swamp Black in the centre.  At first I was going to recommend 5...g6 here, but the main line scores well and is very respectable. }
5... dxe5 6. fxe5 Nc6 7. Be3 Bf5 8. Nc3 e6 9. Nf3 Be7 10. d5
{ White goes for it!  Very rare at 1600 level, but it still pays to know the complications. }
10... exd5 11. cxd5 Nb4 12. Nd4 Bd7 13. e6 fxe6 14. dxe6 Bc6 15. Qg4 Bh4+ 16.
g3 Bxh1 17. Bb5+ { Even sharper than OOO but Black has a good reply } 17... c6
18. O-O-O O-O 19. gxh4 h5
{ Black can't take on b5 because of Nf5 Qf6 Bd4.  But White relies on having his queen on the g file to make this work. Here, if 20 Qxh5 then 20...cb! }
20. Qg6 Qf6 21. Qxf6 Rxf6
{ Black is rewarded for knowing his stuff with the superior position. } *

