[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3
{ This is much more vicious and than the old e3 main line.  Given the chance, White will hit us with e4, and it is best to prevent it, or we end up in a rather nasty line of the Pirc. }
3... d5 4. Nf3
{ This version  (often arrived at via 1 d4 Nf6 2 Nf3 g6  3 Nc3 d5  4 Bf4)  is known as the "Barry attack".  It has been popular in the UK for a long time, mainly due to the efforts of GM Mark Hebden.  I don't see much need to give lines against it specifically at this time though as the themes are very similar to the Nc3 London lines we have seen already and often transpose.    Play  ...Bg7,... OO , ...c5  and take it from there. }
