[Black "The Grob.  Just say no to tasty a- pawns."]
[Result "*"]

1. g4 d5 2. Bg2
{ White hopes you will take on g4.  Which is actually completely playable  . }
2... c6 3. h3
{ White really ought to guard g4 now.  If he plays 3 c4?! then dc is very good for Black. }
3... e5 4. d4 e4 5. c4 Bd6 6. Nc3 Ne7 7. Qb3 a5 8. Bd2
{ Let's let White play something sensible instead.  Because, why wouldn't he? }
8... a4 9. Qc2
{ White decides that if we are offering a pawn, he'd better not take it.  Very sensible.  But we have no objections to keeping it of course.  Black is now better on all areas of the board. }
9... f5 10. e3 O-O
{ White can certainly thrash, but his position is lost.  Is the Grob really as bad as I make out?  Try and find improvements!  Of course there are alternatives - and a determined Grob player will keep investigating them.  More or less at random.  Good luck! }
*

